pageContext.claim: “And, by the way, speaking of China: If you look at the history of China, it was only since they went into the World Trade Organization that they became a rocket ship with their economy. They were flat-lined for years and years. Frankly, for many, many decades.”
pageContext.analysis: China’s rocket-ship-like growth began after opening to foreign trade and implementing free-market reforms in 1979 — more than a decade before joining the World Trade Organization.
